ster already lurks within us. Offering in-depth analysis of numerous films, including The Descent, Outpost, and The Woman in Black, this book takes readers on a lively tour of the genre's highlights, while provocatively exploring how these films reflect viewers' gravest fears about the state of the nation. Whether you are a horror buff, an Anglophile, or an Anglophobe, The Modern British Horror Film is sure to be a thrilling read.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aHorror filmszGreat BritainxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aBritain.  abritish horror.  abritish.  ahorror film.  ahorror movies.  ascary movie.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066608340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9780813579467zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813579467423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813579467.jpg  a978-3-11-066608-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK